    <description>finger for the modern internet — a global, public identity registry queryable from your terminal. Claim a handle, drop a blurb plus an optional ASCII-rendered avatar, and let anyone `whodat` you back. Single static binary, two auth options (password or GitHub OAuth device flow), no feeds.</description>
    <summary>Public identity registry for the terminal — claim a handle, set a blurb, get looked up.</summary>
    <tags>cli terminal finger registry identity rust</tags>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/HueByte/whodat/releases/tag/v__VERSION__</releaseNotes>
